verbose_text: However, treatment of the PCO rats (Group IV) with naringenin at 20 mg/kg resulted in a significant decline in both the 3beta-HSD and 17beta-HSD levels (XREF_FIG)., Naringenin affected the activity of the reactive oxygen species (ROS)-scavenging enzymes, superoxide dismutase (SOD), catalase (CAT), and glutathione peroxidase (GPX), in the rat model of PCOS.
